# Architecture

## Folder layout

- **@layout/** — App shell (main-layout, auth-layout, app-sidebar). No feature business logic.
- **@features/** — One folder per product area (`dashboard`, `investments`, `settings`, `auth`, stubs). Each feature may have `pages/`, `components/`, and `data/`.
- **@core/** — Cross-cutting infra: `auth/` (guards, auth service), `api/` (Supabase, finance, stock, team, errors), `config/` (routes, brand), `utils/`.
- **@shared/** — Reusable UI, pipes, directives, models (no feature-specific flows).

## Import aliases

Use path aliases in `tsconfig.json`: `@core/*`, `@shared/*`, `@layout/*`, `@features/*` (legacy `@app/*` still resolves).

## Conventions

- English folder names; Portuguese **URL paths** stay in `app-routes.ts` / `app.routes.ts`.
- Feature components live under that feature’s `components/`; do not add new code under a removed `finance/` tree.
- Pages are thin: compose feature components and inject `@core/api` services.
